  "texts": [
    "The script ClientHandleRe-motePlayers keeps a list of characters representing other players (more specifically, their CharacterBehaviorController components) and fetches the avatar with the ID specified in the message.",
    "It forwards data to the respective CharacterBehaviorController which implements them.",
    "§ ¤ private void OnPlayerStateUpdate(currentPlayerState msg, Channel channel) { // loop through list ''OtherPlayers'' which references remote players' CharacterBehaviorControllers if (OtherPlayers.TryGetValue(msg.id, out CharacterBehaviorController characterBehaviorController)) { characterBehaviorController.CharacterPosition = msg.characterPosition; characterBehaviorController.CharacterRotation = msg.characterRotation; characterBehaviorController.headIKPosition = msg.headIKPosition; characterBehaviorController.headIKRotation = msg.headIKRotation; characterBehaviorController.lEyeRotation = msg.lEyeRotation; characterBehaviorController.rEyeRotation = msg.rEyeRotation; characterBehaviorController.Smiling = msg.smiling; } } ¦ ¥",
    "Data are written to disk in real-time on the client using logfile writer scripts.",
    "SaveRawData directly notes down data from all active CharacterBehaviorController, i.e., both for one's own avatar and for all other characters."
  ],
